data.title: Three Teams Lead Net Team Championship
data.text:
September 3, 2002 | 3 min.

EDINA, Minn. The teams from Mississippi Dunes GL in Cottage Grove, Koronis Hills GC in Paynesville and Forest Hills GC in Forest Lake hold the lead following first round action at the 10th Minnesota Golf Association (MGA) Net Team Championship held in Nisswa at the Preserve GC Tuesday and the Pines GC Wednesday. All three teams finished the day at a net score of 21-under-par.

The defending champion team of Mississippi Dune GL includes Jason Zilge, Tony Anello and Adam and Andy Palodichuk.

The Koronis Hills team includes Brad Deyak, Steve Fuchs, Randy Beier and Tim Lieser. The team from Forest Lake is represented by Gary, Lisa and Joe Thorvig and Andy Thompson.

Each team fired a 123 total, 21-under-par. The event uses one net best ball score among two, 2-person teams (four players total).

A full field of 44 teams are entered in the championship.
